Overall, when looking at the predictive power amongst the final linear regression model and our final random forest model, the regression model takes the cake. Although neither of the two models are very strong at predicting regular season win percentage, they weren't too bad either. After various tests and hyperparameter tunings, the linear regression model was, on average, within 5.2% of a team's true regular season win percentage, and the random forest model ended up at 5.7%.

